  "response_text": "# Home Workout Plan for Small Spaces\n\n## Weekly Schedule\n\n**Monday: Upper Body Strength**\n- Push-ups (modified on knees if needed)\n- Tricep dips (using a chair)\n- Plank holds\n- Shoulder taps\n- 3 sets, 10-12 reps each\n\n**Tuesday: Cardio & Core**\n- High knees (2 min)\n- Burpees (modified without jump)\n- Mountain climbers\n- Jump rope (or simulate)\n- Bicycle crunches\n- 20-30 min total\n\n**Wednesday: Rest or Gentle Yoga**\n- Stretching routine\n- Light mobility work\n\n**Thursday: Lower Body**\n- Squats\n- Lunges (forward/reverse)\n- Glute bridges\n- Calf raises\n- Wall sits (30 sec holds)\n- 3 sets, 12-15 reps\n\n**Friday: Full Body Circuit**\n- Combine 4-5 exercises from previous days\n- 45 sec work / 15 sec rest intervals\n- 20-25 min total\n\n**Saturday: Active Recovery**\n- Walking, stretching, or yoga\n\n**Sunday: Rest**\n\n## Tips for Success\n- Use resistance bands if available\n- Furniture can substitute for weights (water bottles, backpacks)\n- Focus on form over speed\n- Start with 2-3 workouts weekly and build up\n\nWould you like modifications for any fitness level or specific goals?",
